Global Non-invasive Coronary Imaging Market Insights
Non-invasive Coronary Imaging Market size was valued at USD 2.45 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 4.12 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 6.7% from 2024 to 2030.

Non-invasive Coronary Imaging Market Overview
The Non-invasive Coronary Imaging Market is witnessing robust growth, driven by the increasing demand for advanced cardiovascular diagnostic tools. In 2024, the global market value was estimated at USD 6.5 billion and is projected to reach USD 10.4 billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.3% during the forecast period. This growth can be attributed to rising cardiovascular disease prevalence, the adoption of non-invasive diagnostic technologies, and the increasing need for early detection methods. With advancements in imaging technologies like CT angiography and MRI, the market is expected to experience significant expansion across various regions, driven by rising healthcare investments and improved healthcare infrastructure.

